title: Facebook Faces 2 Irish Probes Over Handing Of Children's Data On Instagram
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) is facing two investigations in Ireland over its handling of children's personal data, Reuters reported Sunday.  What Happened: Graham Doyle, Deputy Commissioner of the Data Protection Commission (DPC) — the main privacy regulator in the European Union — told Reuters that “potential concerns” were identified in how the Mark Zuckerberg-led company processes children's personal data on Instagram.

title: Irish regulator probes Facebook's handling of children's data on Instagram
text: Ireland's Data Protection Commission (DPC) has launched two inquiries into Facebook Inc after concerns were raised about the social network giant's handling of children's personal data on Instagram.
